    <!-- What is Amortization -->
    <div class="content-section">
      <h2>What Is Amortization?</h2>
      <p>
        Amortization is the process of spreading a loan into a series of fixed payments over time. Each payment is split between two components: <strong>interest</strong> (the cost of borrowing) and <strong>principal</strong> (the actual debt repayment). With each successive payment, the interest portion shrinks and the principal portion grows—a characteristic known as the amortization schedule's "tipping point."
      </p>
      <p>
        Think of it this way: when you take out a $300,000 mortgage at 6.5% for 30 years, your monthly payment stays fixed at $1,896. But in month one, $1,625 of that payment goes to interest and only $271 goes toward reducing your balance. By month 180 (the halfway point), the split is roughly equal. And by the final years, nearly the entire payment goes to principal.
      </p>
      <p>
        This applies to <strong>mortgage amortization</strong>, auto loan amortization, student loans, and any fixed-rate installment loan. Understanding your amortization table empowers you to see the true cost of borrowing and make smarter decisions about extra payments, refinancing, or choosing between loan terms.
      </p>

      <h2>The Amortization Formula Explained</h2>
      <p>
        The standard formula for calculating monthly amortization payments is:
      </p>
      <div class="formula-box">
        <code>M = P × [r(1 + r)<sup>n</sup>] / [(1 + r)<sup>n</sup> − 1]</code>
      </div>
      <p>Where:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>M</strong> = Monthly payment amount</li>
        <li><strong>P</strong> = Principal loan amount (the total borrowed)</li>
        <li><strong>r</strong> = Monthly interest rate (annual rate ÷ 12)</li>
        <li><strong>n</strong> = Total number of payments (loan term in years × 12)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Step-by-Step Calculation Example</h3>
      <p>Let's walk through a $250,000 loan at 6% annual interest for 30 years:</p>
      <ol style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;padding-left:1.5rem">
        <li><strong>Convert the annual rate to monthly:</strong> r = 6% ÷ 12 = 0.5% = 0.005</li>
        <li><strong>Calculate total payments:</strong> n = 30 × 12 = 360 months</li>
        <li><strong>Plug into the formula:</strong> M = 250,000 × [0.005 × (1.005)<sup>360</sup>] / [(1.005)<sup>360</sup> − 1]</li>
        <li><strong>Solve (1.005)<sup>360</sup>:</strong> ≈ 6.02258</li>
        <li><strong>Numerator:</strong> 250,000 × [0.005 × 6.02258] = 250,000 × 0.030113 = $7,528.25</li>
        <li><strong>Denominator:</strong> 6.02258 − 1 = 5.02258</li>
        <li><strong>Monthly payment:</strong> M = $7,528.25 ÷ 5.02258 ≈ <strong>$1,498.88</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Over 360 payments, you'd pay $539,595 in total—meaning $289,595 is pure interest. The amortization graph shows how each payment's principal-interest split evolves across these 360 periods.
      </p>

      <h2>How Extra Payments Accelerate Your Payoff</h2>
      <p>
        Extra payments are applied directly to the principal, which has a compounding effect. When you reduce the principal, every future payment's interest charge is smaller—so even more of each subsequent payment goes to principal. This virtuous cycle can dramatically shorten your loan term and reduce total interest paid.
      </p>
      <p>
        For example, adding just $200/month in extra payments to a $300,000 mortgage at 6.5% over 30 years would save you approximately <strong>$62,000 in interest</strong> and pay off the loan nearly <strong>8 years early</strong>. The earlier you start making extra payments, the greater the impact, because you're cutting into the principal during the period when interest charges are highest.
      </p>
      <p>
        Use the calculator above to experiment with different extra payment amounts and see the exact impact on your amortization schedule, total cost, and payoff timeline.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-container">
        {faqItems.map((faq) => (
          <details class="faq-details">
            <summary class="faq-summary">{faq.q}</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>{faq.a}</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section style="max-width:800px;margin:40px auto;padding:0 24px">
    <div style="background:var(--card-bg,#0a1020);border:1px solid var(--border-color,#152040);border-radius:12px;padding:24px">
      <h3 style="font-size:16px;color:var(--text-bright,#fff);margin-bottom:12px">Data Sources & Methodology</h3>
      <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--text-dim,#94a3b8);line-height:1.7;margin:0">Calculations use the standard loan amortization formula. Stat card figures are based on Federal Reserve and industry data for 2025. Results are estimates for educational purposes and should not be used as the sole basis for financial decisions. Always consult a licensed financial advisor for personalized guidance.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="max-width:800px;margin:40px auto;padding:0 24px">
    <h2 style="font-size:20px;color:var(--text-bright,#fff);margin-bottom:16px">Related Pages</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:12px">
      <a href="/annuity-calculator/" style="display:block;padding:16px;background:var(--card-bg,#0a1020);border:1px solid var(--border-color,#152040);border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--text-primary,#c8d0de);transition:transform 0.2s" onmouseover="this.style.transform='translateY(-2px)'" onmouseout="this.style.transform='none'">Annuity Payout Calculator | Estimate Your Retirement Income</a>
      <a href="/compound-interest-calculator/" style="display:block;padding:16px;background:var(--card-bg,#0a1020);border:1px solid var(--border-color,#152040);border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--text-primary,#c8d0de);transition:transform 0.2s" onmouseover="this.style.transform='translateY(-2px)'" onmouseout="this.style.transform='none'">Compound Interest Calculator</a>
      <a href="/bond-calculator/" style="display:block;padding:16px;background:var(--card-bg,#0a1020);border:1px solid var(--border-color,#152040);border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--text-primary,#c8d0de);transition:transform 0.2s" onmouseover="this.style.transform='translateY(-2px)'" onmouseout="this.style.transform='none'">Bond Calculator</a>
      <a href="/real-return-calculator/" style="display:block;padding:16px;background:var(--card-bg,#0a1020);border:1px solid var(--border-color,#152040);border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;color:var(--text-primary,#c8d0de);transition:transform 0.2s" onmouseover="this.style.transform='translateY(-2px)'" onmouseout="this.style.transform='none'">Real Return Calculator: Inflation-Adjusted Returns</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js"></script>
  <script is:inline>
    var areaChart = null;
    var doughnutChart = null;

    function formatUSD(val) {
      return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD', maximumFractionDigits: 0 }).format(val);
    }

    function formatUSD2(val) {
      return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD', maximumFractionDigits: 2 }).format(val);
    }

    function applyPreset(btn) {
      var btns = document.querySelectorAll('.preset-btn');
      for (var i = 0; i < btns.length; i++) { btns[i].classList.remove('active'); }
      btn.classList.add('active');
      document.getElementById('loan-amount').value = btn.getAttribute('data-principal');
      document.getElementById('interest-rate').value = btn.getAttribute('data-rate');
      document.getElementById('loan-term').value = btn.getAttribute('data-term');
      document.getElementById('extra-payment').value = btn.getAttribute('data-extra');
      calculateAmortization();
    }

    function calculateAmortization() {
      var P = parseFloat(document.getElementById('loan-amount').value) || 0;
      var annualRate = parseFloat(document.getElementById('interest-rate').value) || 0;
      var years = parseFloat(document.getElementById('loan-term').value) || 0;
      var extra = parseFloat(document.getElementById('extra-payment').value) || 0;

      if (P <= 0 || years <= 0) {
        document.getElementById('monthly-payment').textContent = '$0.00';
        document.getElementById('stat-total-payments').textContent = '$0.00';
        document.getElementById('stat-total-interest').textContent = '$0.00';
        document.getElementById('stat-payoff-date').textContent = '—';
        document.getElementById('stat-interest-savings').textContent = '$0.00';
        document.getElementById('schedule-section').style.display = 'none';
        return;
      }

      var r = annualRate / 100 / 12;
      var n = Math.round(years * 12);
      var monthlyPayment = 0;

      if (r === 0) {
        monthlyPayment = P / n;
      } else {
        monthlyPayment = P * (r * Math.pow(1 + r, n)) / (Math.pow(1 + r, n) - 1);
      }

      document.getElementById('monthly-payment').textContent = formatUSD2(monthlyPayment);

      // Generate schedule WITHOUT extra payments (baseline)
      var baselineTotalInterest = 0;
      var baseBalance = P;
      for (var bi = 0; bi < n; bi++) {
        var baseInt = baseBalance * r;
        var basePrin = monthlyPayment - baseInt;
        baselineTotalInterest += baseInt;
        baseBalance -= basePrin;
        if (baseBalance < 0) baseBalance = 0;
      }

      // Generate schedule WITH extra payments
      var schedule = [];
      var balance = P;
      var totalInterest = 0;
      var totalPaid = 0;
      var principalByMonth = [];
      var interestByMonth = [];
      var labels = [];
      var month = 0;

      while (balance > 0.01 && month < n * 2) {
        month++;
        var intPayment = balance * r;
        var prinPayment = monthlyPayment - intPayment;
        var actualExtra = extra;

        if (prinPayment + actualExtra >= balance) {
          prinPayment = balance - intPayment;
          if (prinPayment < 0) prinPayment = 0;
          actualExtra = Math.max(0, balance - prinPayment);
          var thisPayment = intPayment + prinPayment + (balance - prinPayment > 0 ? balance - prinPayment - prinPayment : 0);
          // recalc: just pay off the rest
          actualExtra = 0;
          var remaining = balance;
          prinPayment = remaining * (remaining / (remaining + intPayment));
          // simpler: just close it out
          prinPayment = balance;
          intPayment = balance * r;
          var lastPmt = intPayment + prinPayment;
          actualExtra = 0;
          totalInterest += intPayment;
          totalPaid += lastPmt;
          schedule.push({ month: month, payment: lastPmt, principal: prinPayment, interest: intPayment, extra: 0, balance: 0 });
          principalByMonth.push(prinPayment);
          interestByMonth.push(intPayment);
          labels.push(month);
          balance = 0;
          break;
        }

        totalInterest += intPayment;
        totalPaid += monthlyPayment + actualExtra;
        balance -= (prinPayment + actualExtra);
        if (balance < 0) balance = 0;

        schedule.push({
          month: month,
          payment: monthlyPayment + actualExtra,
          principal: prinPayment,
          interest: intPayment,
          extra: actualExtra,
          balance: balance
        });

        principalByMonth.push(prinPayment);
        interestByMonth.push(intPayment);
        labels.push(month);
      }

      // Summary stats
      document.getElementById('stat-total-payments').textContent = formatUSD(totalPaid);
      document.getElementById('stat-total-interest').textContent = formatUSD(totalInterest);

      var now = new Date();
      var payoffDate = new Date(now.getFullYear(), now.getMonth() + schedule.length, 1);
      var payoffStr = payoffDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', year: 'numeric' });
      document.getElementById('stat-payoff-date').textContent = payoffStr;

      var savings = baselineTotalInterest - totalInterest;
      if (savings > 0.5) {
        document.getElementById('stat-interest-savings').textContent = formatUSD(savings);
      } else {
        document.getElementById('stat-interest-savings').textContent = '$0';
      }

      // Build table
      var tbody = document.getElementById('amort-tbody');
      var html = '';
      for (var si = 0; si < schedule.length; si++) {
        var row = schedule[si];
        html += '<tr>' +
          '<td>' + row.month + '</td>' +
          '<td>' + formatUSD2(row.payment) + '</td>' +
          '<td>' + formatUSD2(row.principal) + '</td>' +
          '<td>' + formatUSD2(row.interest) + '</td>' +
          '<td>' + (row.extra > 0 ? formatUSD2(row.extra) : '—') + '</td>' +
          '<td>' + formatUSD2(row.balance) + '</td>' +
          '</tr>';
      }
      tbody.innerHTML = html;
      document.getElementById('schedule-section').style.display = 'block';

      // Charts — sample every N months for performance
      var step = schedule.length > 120 ? Math.floor(schedule.length / 60) : 1;
      var chartLabels = [];
      var chartPrin = [];
      var chartInt = [];
      for (var ci = 0; ci < schedule.length; ci += step) {
        chartLabels.push('Mo ' + schedule[ci].month);
        chartPrin.push(Math.round(principalByMonth[ci] * 100) / 100);
        chartInt.push(Math.round(interestByMonth[ci] * 100) / 100);
      }

      // Area chart
      var areaCtx = document.getElementById('amort-area-chart').getContext('2d');
      if (areaChart) areaChart.destroy();
      areaChart = new Chart(areaCtx, {
        type: 'line',
        data: {
          labels: chartLabels,
          datasets: [
            {
              label: 'Principal',
              data: chartPrin,
              borderColor: '#10b981',
              backgroundColor: 'rgba(16,185,129,0.15)',
              fill: true,
              tension: 0.3,
              pointRadius: 0
            },
            {
              label: 'Interest',
              data: chartInt,
              borderColor: '#ef4444',
              backgroundColor: 'rgba(239,68,68,0.15)',
              fill: true,
              tension: 0.3,
              pointRadius: 0
            }
          ]
        },
        options: {
          responsive: true,
          maintainAspectRatio: false,
          plugins: {
            legend: { labels: { color: '#c8d0de' } },
            tooltip: {
              callbacks: {
                label: function(ctx) { return ctx.dataset.label + ': $' + ctx.parsed.y.toFixed(2); }
              }
            }
          },
          scales: {
            x: { ticks: { color: '#94a3b8', maxTicksLimit: 12 }, grid: { color: 'rgba(48,54,61,0.5)' } },
            y: { ticks: { color: '#94a3b8', callback: function(v) { return '$' + v.toLocaleString(); } }, grid: { color: 'rgba(48,54,61,0.5)' } }
          }
        }
      });

      // Doughnut chart
      var doughCtx = document.getElementById('amort-doughnut-chart').getContext('2d');
      if (doughnutChart) doughnutChart.destroy();
      doughnutChart = new Chart(doughCtx, {
        type: 'doughnut',
        data: {
          labels: ['Total Principal', 'Total Interest'],
          datasets: [{
            data: [Math.round(P), Math.round(totalInterest)],
            backgroundColor: ['#4a8fe7', '#ef4444'],
            borderColor: ['#4a8fe7', '#ef4444'],
            borderWidth: 1
          }]
        },
        options: {
          responsive: true,
          maintainAspectRatio: false,
          plugins: {
            legend: { labels: { color: '#c8d0de' } },
            tooltip: {
              callbacks: {
                label: function(ctx) {
                  var total = 0;
                  for (var di = 0; di < ctx.dataset.data.length; di++) { total += ctx.dataset.data[di]; }
                  var pct = ((ctx.parsed / total) * 100).toFixed(1);
                  return ctx.label + ': $' + ctx.parsed.toLocaleString() + ' (' + pct + '%)';
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      });
    }

    function initAmortCalc() {
      var form = document.getElementById('amort-form');
      if (!form || form.dataset.initialized) return;
      form.dataset.initialized = 'true';

      var inputs = form.querySelectorAll('input');
      for (var ii = 0; ii < inputs.length; ii++) {
        inputs[ii].addEventListener('input', calculateAmortization);
      }

      calculateAmortization();
    }

    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initAmortCalc);
    document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initAmortCalc);
  </script>

